issue.title: Replicating Caffe performance?
issue.body:
Hi @ildoonet , thanks for sharing the nice code!

I wonder how you can replicate the numbers by training from scratch. I load vgg pretrained, lr=1e-4, batch_size=16, I trained for ~140k iterations and found the training loss basically converged. Then I test it on val2014, but I only got AP=0.3360.

Can you share your settings?

comment.body:
Replicating the Caffe performantce seems to be a long road ahead, so I try to list some of the problems I could find so far, and keep updating the list as I move along. Here are some of the differences between the original caffe code and the code in this repository: First some links to the original training code for vgg19 (first 10 layers) as backbone reaching 58.80% on coco val 2017 (multiscale evaluation) and 48.99 % mAP (single scale evaluation) [pose_train_test.prototxt](https://github.com/ZheC/Realtime_Multi-Person_Pose_Estimation/blob/master/training/example_proto/pose_train_test.prototxt), shows the original architecture, as well as preprocessing steps, learning rate multipliers, gaussian weight initializers and weight decay parameters [pose_solver.prototxt](https://github.com/ZheC/Realtime_Multi-Person_Pose_Estimation/blob/master/training/example_proto/pose_solver.prototxt), specifies optimizer and lr policy (default optimizer in Caffe is SGD with momentum)   | TFPE (this repo) | CMU (original caffe version) -- | -- | -- preprocessing | flipcrop_xy = 432x368
rotate: 15°
scale_min: 0.8
scale_max: 1.2| stride: 8    
max_rotate_degree: 40   
crop_size_x: 368   
crop_size_y: 368    
scale_prob: 1    
scale_min: 0.5    
scale_max: 1.1    
target_dist: 0.6 <- ???    
center_perterb_max: 40 <- ???
???: probably computed based on some bounding box values weight initialization |   | gaussian, stdev=0.01 (conv)constant (bias) learning rate multiplier | none | 1.0 for base weights
2.0 for base bias
4.0 for CPM + Mconv weights
8.0 for CPM + Mconv weights optimizer | Adam | SGD + Momentum (0.9) learning rate | 0.001 | 4e-05 lr policy | cosine decay | step (after 10 Epochs?) weight decay | none | 5e-4
decay_mult_conv = 1
decay_mult_bias = 0 batch size | 64? 32! | 10 losses | l2 loss averaged over all stages
(only 6 are used!?) using ‘reduce mean’ for both heatmap and paf
paf and heatmap loss are averaged
the division by batchsize is ‘wrong’ in case of multi-gpu training | only paf loss for all 6 stages
heatmap loss in last stage only (since 30.05.2019) background class | learns a background class:
1 - max(heatmap, axis=2)→ total of 19 classes | not mentioned here!?
